77 template <typename T>
78 class handle_traits {};
79 
93 template <typename T, typename traits = handle_traits<T>>
94 class handle {
95 private:
96  static dnnl_status_t dummy_destructor(T) { return dnnl_success; }
97 
98  std::shared_ptr<typename std::remove_pointer<T>::type> _data;
99  handle(const handle &&) = delete;
100  handle &operator=(const handle &&other) = delete;
101 
102 protected:
103  bool operator==(const T other) const { return other == _data.get(); }
104  bool operator!=(const T other) const { return !(*this == other); }
105 
106 public:
110  handle(T t, bool weak = false) : _data(0) { reset(t, weak); }
111 
121  handle() : handle((T)0, true) {}
122 
123  handle(const handle &other) : _data(other._data) {}
124  handle &operator=(const handle &other) {
125  _data = other._data;
126  return *this;
127  }
131  void reset(T t, bool weak = false) {
132  _data.reset(t, weak ? &dummy_destructor : traits::destructor);
133  }
134 
136  T get(bool allow_emtpy = false) const {
137  T result = _data.get();
138 
139  if (allow_emtpy == false && result == nullptr)
140  throw dnnl::error(dnnl_invalid_arguments,
141  "attempt to use uninitialized object");
142 
143  return result;
144  }
145 
146  bool operator==(const handle &other) const {
147  return other._data.get() == _data.get();
148  }
149  bool operator!=(const handle &other) const { return !(*this == other); }
150 };

412 #define DNNL_DEFINE_BITMASK_OPS(enum_name) \
413  inline enum_name operator|(enum_name lhs, enum_name rhs) { \
414  return static_cast<enum_name>( \
415  static_cast<unsigned>(lhs) | static_cast<unsigned>(rhs)); \
416  } \
417 \
418  inline enum_name operator&(enum_name lhs, enum_name rhs) { \
419  return static_cast<enum_name>( \
420  static_cast<unsigned>(lhs) & static_cast<unsigned>(rhs)); \
421  } \
422 \
423  inline enum_name operator^(enum_name lhs, enum_name rhs) { \
424  return static_cast<enum_name>( \
425  static_cast<unsigned>(lhs) ^ static_cast<unsigned>(rhs)); \
426  } \
427 \
428  inline enum_name &operator|=(enum_name &lhs, enum_name rhs) { \
429  lhs = static_cast<enum_name>( \
430  static_cast<unsigned>(lhs) | static_cast<unsigned>(rhs)); \
431  return lhs; \
432  } \
433 \
434  inline enum_name &operator&=(enum_name &lhs, enum_name rhs) { \
435  lhs = static_cast<enum_name>( \
436  static_cast<unsigned>(lhs) & static_cast<unsigned>(rhs)); \
437  return lhs; \
438  } \
439 \
440  inline enum_name &operator^=(enum_name &lhs, enum_name rhs) { \
441  lhs = static_cast<enum_name>( \
442  static_cast<unsigned>(lhs) ^ static_cast<unsigned>(rhs)); \
443  return lhs; \
444  } \
445 \
446  inline enum_name operator~(enum_name rhs) { \
447  return static_cast<enum_name>(~static_cast<unsigned>(rhs)); \
448  }

971  static_cast<unsigned>(lhs) | static_cast<unsigned>(rhs));
972 }
973 
974 inline stream::flags operator&(stream::flags lhs, stream::flags rhs) {
975  return static_cast<stream::flags>(
976  static_cast<unsigned>(lhs) & static_cast<unsigned>(rhs));
977 }

981  static_cast<unsigned>(lhs) ^ static_cast<unsigned>(rhs));
982 }

1341  struct desc {
1342  friend struct memory;
1344  dnnl_memory_desc_t data;
1345 
1347  desc() : data() {}
1348 
1354  desc(const dims &adims, data_type adata_type, format_tag aformat_tag) {
1355  validate_dims(adims);
1356  error::wrap_c_api(
1357  dnnl_memory_desc_init_by_tag(&data, (int)adims.size(),
1358  adims.size() == 0 ? nullptr : &adims[0],
1359  convert_to_c(adata_type),
1360  convert_to_c(aformat_tag)),
1361  "could not initialize a memory descriptor by tag");
1362  }
1363 
1369  desc(const dims &adims, data_type adata_type, const dims &astrides) {
1370  validate_dims(adims);
1371  error::wrap_c_api(
1372  dnnl_memory_desc_init_by_strides(&data, (int)adims.size(),
1373  adims.size() == 0 ? nullptr : &adims[0],
1374  convert_to_c(adata_type),
1375  astrides.size() == 0 ? nullptr : &astrides[0]),
1376  "could not initialize a memory descriptor by strides");
1377  }
1378 
1382  desc(const dnnl_memory_desc_t &adata) : data(adata) {}
1383 
1385  //
1388  desc submemory_desc(const dims &adims, const dims &offsets) {
1389  dnnl_memory_desc_t sub_md;
1390  error::wrap_c_api(dnnl_memory_desc_init_submemory(
1391  &sub_md, &data, &adims[0], &offsets[0]),
1392  "could not initialize a sub-memory");
1393  return desc(sub_md);
1394  }
1395 
1398  size_t get_size() const { return dnnl_memory_desc_get_size(&data); }
1399 
1401  bool is_zero() const { return data.ndims == 0; }
1402 
1403  bool operator==(const desc &other) const {
1404  return dnnl_memory_desc_equal(&data, &other.data) != 0;
1405  }
1406 
1407  bool operator!=(const desc &other) const { return !operator==(other); }
1408  };
1409 
1410  memory() = default;
1411 
1417  memory(const desc &md, const engine &aengine, void *ahandle) {
1418  dnnl_memory_t result;
1419  error::wrap_c_api(
1420  dnnl_memory_create(&result, &md.data, aengine.get(), ahandle),
1421  "could not create a memory");
1422  reset(result);
1423  }
1424 
1429  memory(const desc &md, const engine &aengine)
1430  : memory(md, aengine, DNNL_MEMORY_ALLOCATE) {}
1431 
1433  desc get_desc() const {
1434  const dnnl_memory_desc_t *cdesc;
1435  error::wrap_c_api(dnnl_memory_get_memory_desc(get(), &cdesc),
1436  "could not get memory descriptor from a memory");
1437  return desc(*cdesc);
1438  }

1444  "could not get engine from a memory");
1445  return engine(engine_q);

1813 struct primitive_desc : public handle<dnnl_primitive_desc_t> {
1814  primitive_desc() = default;
1815 
1819  primitive_desc(const_dnnl_op_desc_t desc, const primitive_attr *attr,
1820  const engine &e, const_dnnl_primitive_desc_t hint_fwd_pd) {
1821  dnnl_primitive_desc_iterator_t iterator = nullptr;
1822  dnnl_status_t status = dnnl_primitive_desc_iterator_create(&iterator,
1823  desc, attr ? attr->get() : nullptr, e.get(), hint_fwd_pd);
1824  error::wrap_c_api(
1825  status, "could not create a primitive descriptor iterator");
1826  pd_iterator.reset(iterator);
1827  fetch_impl();
1828  }
1829 
1830  engine get_engine() { return engine::query(*this); }
1831 
1832  primitive_attr get_primitive_attr() const {
1833  const_dnnl_primitive_attr_t const_cattr;
1834  error::wrap_c_api(dnnl_primitive_desc_get_attr(get(), &const_cattr),
1835  "could not get attributes");
1836  dnnl_primitive_attr_t cattr;
1837  error::wrap_c_api(dnnl_primitive_attr_clone(&cattr, const_cattr),
1838  "could not clone attributes");
1839 
1840  primitive_attr attr;
1841  attr.reset(cattr);
1842  return attr;
1843  }
1844 
1846  const char *impl_info_str() const {
1847  const char *res;
1848  error::wrap_c_api(dnnl_primitive_desc_query(
1849  get(), dnnl_query_impl_info_str, 0, &res),
1850  "could not query implementation info string");
1851  return res;
1852  }
1853 
1855  memory::dim query_s64(query q) const {
1856  memory::dim res;
1857  dnnl_status_t status = dnnl_primitive_desc_query(
1858  get(), dnnl::convert_to_c(q), 0, &res);
1859  return status == dnnl_success ? res : 0;
1860  }
1861 
1868  bool next_impl() {
1869  dnnl_status_t status
1870  = dnnl_primitive_desc_iterator_next(pd_iterator.get());
1871  if (status == dnnl_iterator_ends) return false;
1872  error::wrap_c_api(status, "primitive descriptor iterator next failed");
1873 
1874  fetch_impl();
1875  return true;
1876  }
1877 
1879  memory::desc query_md(query what, int idx = 0) const {
1880  std::vector<query> valid_q {query::src_md, query::diff_src_md,
1881  query::weights_md, query::diff_weights_md, query::dst_md,
1882  query::diff_dst_md, query::workspace_md, query::scratchpad_md};
1883  if (!std::any_of(valid_q.cbegin(), valid_q.cend(),
1884  [=](query q) { return what == q; }))
1885  throw error(dnnl_invalid_arguments, "invalid memory query");
1886 
1887  const dnnl_memory_desc_t *cdesc = dnnl_primitive_desc_query_md(
1888  get(), dnnl::convert_to_c(what), idx);
1889  return memory::desc(*cdesc);
1890  }
1891 
1896  memory::desc scratchpad_desc() const {
1897  return query_md(query::scratchpad_md, 0);
1898  }
1899 
1900 private:
1901  handle<dnnl_primitive_desc_iterator_t> pd_iterator;
1902  void fetch_impl() {
1903  dnnl_primitive_desc_t pd
1904  = dnnl_primitive_desc_iterator_fetch(pd_iterator.get());
1905  error::wrap_c_api(pd != nullptr ? dnnl_success : dnnl_runtime_error,
1906  "could not fetch a primitive descriptor from the iterator");
1907  reset(pd);
1908  }
